        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=48442&amp;TOPIC_ID=5932&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Fear%2FSnare+bad+luck+algorythm&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Invoke Fear lasts a maximum of 42s, Dooming lasts 90s.</P><P>Take this spell casting line-up for example:<BR>Dooming<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>Splurt 4s cast time<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>Pyro 5.5s cast time<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>Vex 5.5s cast time<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>Invoke Fear 2.5s cast time</P><P>By the time Fear lands, Dooming has about 52s left on the timer. So, taking into account lag issues, etc, Fear will seem to run out coincidentally close to Dooming.</P><P>Or take this one:<BR>Dooming<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>Pyro 5.5s cast time<BR>run/stand still 5s<BR>CoC 5s cast time<BR>Fear 2.5s cast time</P><P>With this set-up, Fear runs out about 20s before Dooming (and Dooming runs out 10s after CoC, which I find to be a fairly useful timer). So, a recasted Fear would last about 24s till Dooming wore off, which is half the total duration. Given that it's a 7 tick spell that is checked every tick, having it last 3-4 ticks doesn't seem all that unlikely.</P><P>So, it doesn't seem to me that there's coding that makes it more likely for random duration spells wear off when another spell wears off. However, I do think they decided to make the timing of the spells such that a few of the more synergistic ones (snare/root/fear) would tend to run out at the same time. This was probably done to reduce the triviality of snare/root/fear combos so that a wrench gets occasionally gets thrown into the works.</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
